commitmsg:
Set up react-router and make basic customizations

Set up react-router, add a basic homepage, lay the groundwork for future
dashboards, and remove assets from create-react-app that are not needed.

Initial create-react-app skeleton

This is the result of running `create-react-app ensemble` and doing
nothing else.
Use suggestedMin and suggestedMax from the data
Set different highestY and lowestY padding values
Fix #37: Shrink the range of the y axis
Use commas for y values >= 1,000 in rollover
Link from usage dashboard to private demo
Fix lines, areas, and legends in dark theme

Fix broken Heroku builds

Heroku has been complaining that yarn.lock is out of date with
package.json. This commit should fix that.

Merge pull request #36 from mozilla/theming

usage report theming
Fix #20: Upgrade react and react-dom to v16

Merge pull request #38 from mozilla/renovate/react-metrics-graphics-1.x

Update dependency react-metrics-graphics to v1.0.2

Merge pull request #35 from mozilla/renovate/pin-dependencies

Pin dependency dateformat to v3.0.3
For now, show the "all" category by default

Remove greenkeeper-lockfile dependency

We have since switched from Greenkeeper to Renovate.

Disable CircleCI

This was only enabled because Greenkeeper required it. It never ran real
tests. We have since switched to Renovate, which does not have this
requirement.

Merge pull request #27 from mozilla/renovate/pin-dependencies

Pin Dependencies
Remove reference to Main.css in Main.js

Merge pull request #26 from mozilla/renovate/configure

Configure Renovate
Fix spacing on "Usage dashboard missing" text
Inform users that the usage page is private
Add config/ directory for specifying dashboards

Temporarily disable the create-react-app buildpack

Production builds are not currently possible due to a bug with
react-metric-graphics.[1] Hopefully this stops Heroku from attempting
production builds, allowing us to push again.

[1] https://github.com/mozilla/react-metrics-graphics/issues/18

Only customize population colors for 11+ pops

metrics-graphics sets some nice distinct colors for charts with 1-10
populations.

Fix color of text that appears upon hover

Make the color of this text match the color of the corresponding line.

Issue #19: Give each population a unique color

This is a workaround for [1].

[1] https://github.com/mozilla/metrics-graphics/issues/806
Upgrade to the latest version of metrics-graphics
Don't show data points when y value is null

Disable automatic refreshing

I'm not certain, but this may be causing the performance issues some are
seeing.
Support JSON that doesn't specify sections
Fix #17: Re-implement layout without CSS Grid
Add usage dashboard, change user-facing name

Disallow search engines, add proof of concept note

Ensemble is currently hosting a version of the Firefox Hardware Report
data, but only as a proof of concept. I don't want anyone to become
confused and think that this is the official site for the Hardware
Report.
Add prototype Firefox Hardware Report dashboard
Use a version range (^) for react-scripts
Launch Firefox when running site locally
Add jquery, a peerDependency of metrics-graphics

Update yarn.lock (again)

I made a mistake in the last update and yarn.lock ended up being
out-of-sync with package.json, resulting in the Heroku build failing.

Merge pull request #8 from mozilla/circleci-generate-lockfile

Generate lockfile on CircleCI

Update yarn.lock

I'm not sure why Greenkeeper didn't do this itself. I forgot to check
for that. In any case, here it is now.

Merge pull request #7 from mozilla/greenkeeper/react-scripts-1.0.17

Update react-scripts to the latest version ðŸš€

Downgrade react and react-dom

For some reason, react-metrics-graphics doesn't support version 16 of
either of these packages.

Remove Greenkeeper badge

I'm not sure what purpose it serves, really. Visitors to this page
probably don't care whether Greenkeeper is enabled.

Merge pull request #3 from mozilla/greenkeeper/initial

Update dependencies to enable Greenkeeper ðŸŒ´

Manually update yarn.lock

According to Greenkeeper support, this needs to be done manually in the
first Greenkeeper pull request.
Add a version number to the example JSON
Fix links and some code cleanup

Call for registrations on the homepage

Ensemble is ready to host real data, even if the dashboards are
currently fairly simple, so a note is added to the homepage requesting
calls for submissions.
Add longer descriptions for example charts

Move "example data" warning to dashboard pages

Ensemble is almost ready to start hosting real data, even if the
dashboards for that data are pretty simple. So I'd like to start
treating it like a real product. The data warning won't affect all of
our datasets that Ensemble can host, only example datasets, so it should
be shown there.
Fix link to GitHub project page
Add dummy header, dummy homepage, and warning
Show descriptions, use CSS Grid, some refactoring
